<title>BELGIUM: Commission says to probe Swiss Re's Uniorias buy.</title>
<headline>Commission says to probe Swiss Re's Uniorias buy.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-01-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>The European Commission said on Friday it was starting a routine probe into the acquisition of Italian reinsurer Uniorias by Swiss Re, it said in a statement.</p>
<p>&quot;Upon preliminary examination, the Commission finds that the notified concentration could fall within the scope of the (EU merger regulation),&quot; the Commission said.</p>
<p>Swiss Re signed a deal to purchase Unione di Riassicurazione SpA last month, saying it would buy it from Instituto Nazionale delle Assicurazoni SpA (INA) for an expected price of 500 million Swiss francs.</p>
<p>The Commission said it received notification of the deal under EU merger rules on January 9. It has one month to clear it or start an in-depth inquiry if it is concerned about the effects of competition.</p>
